%META:TOPICPARENT{name="TdwgSecretariat"}%
---++Journal Editors

Please add, modify or comment.

---+++Volunteers from St Louis

Lee Belbin, Gail Kampmeier, Arturo Ariño, Éamonn Ó Tuama, Rebecca Shapley, Anna Weitzman

Editor 2007: Anna Weitzman 
Sub Editors (2007): Lee Belbin, Gail Kampmeier, Arturo Ariño

---+++Roles and Responsibilities

   1. The Editor of the Proceedings of TDWG (& Charters, Standards track?)
   1. In consultation with the Annual Conference Manager, arranges Session Chairs as Section Editors to manage submissions in their session (peer review through copyediting)
   1. Ensures that documentation for Section Editors, authors, reviewers and readers is current and effective
   1. Liaises with the Annual Conference Manager and Sysadmin on the preparation and publication of the Proceedings of TDWG

---+++Tasks for 2007

   1. Maintain expertise in managing and using OJS - the Online Journal System that supports the Proceedings of TDWG.
   1. Update the policy on submissions (Instructions for Authors). How to format titles (cap first), Authors (firstname lastname), affiliations (institution, location city). Maximum abstract length. Steps for submission and review.
   1. Update 'Instructions for Editors' and ensure it is distributed to Session Chairs when they are announced. 
   1. Write 'Instructions for Session Chairs' and ensure it is distributed to Session Chairs when they are announced.
   1. Be prepared to assist Section Editors and Authors with OJS and remind them of their responsibilities.
   1. Submit errors in OJS to Sysadmin, track progress and resolution.
   1. Lead the preparation and publication of the Annual Conference Abstracts volume with assistance from Annual Conference Manager and Sysadmin

Further information can be obtained from Lee Belbin (lee-at-tdwg-dot-org)


-- Main.LeeBelbin - 22 Nov 2006
